2003_July 22 

There is very little way to quantify how good this movie is. Its like
describing how water is wet or how politicians are corrupt. they just are.
This movie articulates the rage and bile that many american males feel
today. It may not be pretty, it may not be what you want to hear, but you
need to hear it to understand. The direction is Fincher's best. The script
is superb. Norton and Pitt give their best performances, which has made them
pretentious as of late, but this is great. a perfect 10

